13:
Eat it. 
I promise there's no poison inside.
17:
Another person fleeing... Do I still
smell of blood? Even a change of
clothes does nothing to hide the
stench...
22:
Yeah, it's not the stench. The suit just
makes him look suspicious...
26:
My apologies. I thought it best to
have him wear more formal attire,
but I should have foreseen this
possibility.
29: Hey... The hell is he doing?
33:
I asked before, and I guess this is his
way of thanking the person he
received chocolates from on
Valentine's Fest.
37:
Evidently, a new festival called White
Fest has grown popular. It involves a
tradition where one gives something
back to anyone who they received
chocolate from.
41:
The chocolate he got was from a
staff member at that sweet shop,
which is why he's helping out.
46:
Is that so? Never took him for the
popular ty—
49:
Wait... Didn't EVERYONE get
chocolate from that shop? Pretty
sure they were just handing out
samples.
54:
Yeah, that's right... But no matter
how many times we explained it,
Klaus insisted that he always
"repays his debts."
60:
How can anyone be that dense...
But, well, that does explain the
get-up and bad sales pitches.
63:
K-Klaus, you know... I-I think you've
done more than enough to thank
me now, so why don't we call it a
day and—
67:
No, my work here is not yet
complete. You need not pity me.
70:
I-in that case, could you do some
shopping for me instead?
71:
I need more powdered sugar. Just
pure powdered sugar! Nothing
special! It should look like a white
powder.
79:
I heard you sell white powder here.
The pure stuff. Hand it over.
85: Do you take me for a fool?
90:
Whoa, wait, there's been a
misunderstanding! We're looking for
pure powdered sugar!
96:
Sorry, we shouldn't have been
spying on you.
99:
It's fine. I could smell you the whole
time... But it seems I have failed in
my task.
103:
Perhaps this is one debt I cannot
repay...
108:
Are you truly okay with that, Klaus?
Or do you wish to change?
111:
Your manners just come off a bit
uncouth. If you so wish, I can give a
crash course in etiquette.
116:
Sounds like another debt I'll have to
repay.
123:
Try one of our polar bear cookies. 
If you enjoy it, stop by the bakery 
over there.
129: Please take a polar bear cookie.
132:
Wow, it's so cute! They're selling
them over there, right? Thank you!
139:
That's much better. I don't know if I'd
call him the perfect gentleman, but
close enough...
146:
That was amazing, Klaus! Thanks to
you, we've completely sold out!
154:
Nice work today! How'd you like
handing out treats?
158:
I just did what was required of me.
Now my debt is repaid.
161:
But... This was a very strange
experience. I don't know how to
explain it.
165: It wasn't a bad time at least, right?
170:
Perhaps you could help out
tomorrow as well, Klaus.
178:
I am merely suggesting you do what
feels right.
181:
Yeah, why not give it a go? Could be
nice to step out of your comfort
zone and see what you find.
187:
Fine, I suppose it doesn't sound so
bad.
